<h2 class="slug">Digital Life</h2>
<h3>#Gamergate Controversy Fuels Debate On Women And Video Games</h3>
</div>
<div class="storyimg"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2014/09/24/istock_000007740942medium_sq-eff1a9d103c29332b9787a65815dfb06d0db2edf.jpg?s=16" alt="Under the #Gamergate hashtag, a debate has flared surrounding ethics in video game journalism and the role and treatment of women in the video game industry."></div></a></article><article id="story351192506" class="story clearfix"><a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/alltechconsidered/2014/09/24/351192506/some-iphone-6-plus-users-find-an-unwanted-feature-it-bends" data-metrics='{"category" : "Story to Story", "action" : "Click Egg Carton", "label" : "http://www.npr.org/blogs/alltechconsidered/2014/09/24/351192506/some-iphone-6-plus-users-find-an-unwanted-feature-it-bends"}'><div class="storyinfo">
<h2 class="slug">Technology</h2>
<h3>Some iPhone 6 Plus Users Find An Unwanted Feature: It Bends</h3>
</div>
